<h2><a name="seekg" id="seekg">seekg</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;fstream&gt;</span>
    istream<span class="sy0">&amp;</span> istream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">seekg</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> off_type offset<span class="sy0">,</span> ios<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">seekdir</span> origin <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    istream<span class="sy0">&amp;</span> istream<span class="sy0">::</span><span class="me2">seekg</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> pos_type position <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The function seekg() is used with input streams, and it repositions the “get”
pointer for the current stream to offset bytes away from origin, or places the
“get” pointer at position.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="seekp" class="wikilink1" title="io:seekp">seekp</a>, <a href="tellg" class="wikilink1" title="io:tellg">tellg</a>, <a href="tellp" class="wikilink1" title="io:tellp">tellp</a>, <a href="seekdir" class="wikilink1" title="io:seekdir">seekdir</a>
</p>

